<HEADLINE>
TEXAS-ARLINGTON FORWARD FINDING COLLEGE BASKETBALL DEMANDING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DARRIN SCHEID 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ The knock on Texas-Arlington junior forward
Dewayne Marable is that he could work a little harder.
</P>
<P>
   This comes from a pretty good source _ Marable.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wasn't used to this when I came here from junior college,''
he said. ``This is a lot more demanding. I don't know how to
explain it, except that I need to do more in practice. I need to
work harder in games.''
</P>
<P>
   The revelation for Marable, a 6-foot-8, 215-pound forward from
Lawson State (Ala.) Community College, comes at a time when
teammates and coaches say they need him most. Texas-Arlington
starting forward Bill Washington has played fewer minutes the past
two weeks because of a back injury.
</P>
<P>
   Junior-college recruit Leonard Osborn did not gain eligibility.
That leaves one player on Texas-Arlington's bench taller than 6-5.
</P>
<P>
   That guy is Marable, and he might be the key to Texas-Arlington
turning around a frustrating season and making a run at the
Southland Conference tournament. The Mavericks (5-11, 3-5 in
conference) are eighth in the SLC. Six teams go to the tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dewayne has improved a lot this season, and that has to do
with him not worrying so much,'' said Keith Greene,
Texas-Arlington's leading scorer and Marable's roommate. ``He
stopped thinking about what coaches are going to say to him and
just started playing basketball. We need him. He's the only other
big man we have.''
</P>
<P>
   Marable was high on Texas-Arlington coach Eddie McCarter's wish
list in the late signing period last year. After waiting until the
night before signing day, Marable choose Texas-Arlington over
Jacksonville and Middle Tennessee.
</P>
<P>
   At times, he has lived up to his repTexas-Arlingtontion of an
athletic big man with a good shooting touch.
</P>
<P>
   In five of Texas-Arlington's past eight games, Marable has
scored in double figures, including a 19-point performance against
UT-San Antonio. In conference games, he is averaging 11.4 points
and 5.4 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Texas-Arlington coaches might even move Marable into the
starting lineup for Saturday's 7:30 p.m. game at Nicholls State.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dewayne needed some time to get used to Division I
basketball,'' Texas-Arlington assistant coach Tony Stubblefield
said. ``He still needs to get stronger, but Dewayne has looked a
lot better in the past few games. He's going stronger to the basket
and doing things we expected him to do.''
</P>
<P>
   Marable said he has waited a long time for some good things to
happen for him.
</P>
<P>
   His first game at Texas-Arlington was against Baylor, and
Marable turned in a 1-for-13 performance in Texas-Arlington's 64-59
loss.
</P>
<P>
   He had six points in Texas-Arlington's 66-45 loss against
Southwest Texas State's 6-11 center Jeff Foster.
</P>
<P>
   A 47 percent shooter from the 3-point line in junior college, he
is currently 0-for-14.
</P>
<P>
   ``That game against Baylor still bothers me,'' Marable said.
``Every time I see them on television, I think about how I played
in that game and how we should have won. I lost it for us.''
</P>
<P>
   Teammates remind Marable that he helped win the SLC opener
against Sam Houston State. He wasn't supposed to play because he
missed practice the day before, but the game went to triple
overtime.
</P>
<P>
   Marable scored eight points in the first overtime, and
Texas-Arlington left with a 125-123 victory.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm being asked to do the same things I did in junior
college,'' Marable said. ``The difference is the speed of the game
and the intensity. Those are things I'm still getting use to. It's
a lot harder. It's more work.''
</P>
<P>
   (Darrin Scheid writes about colleges for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. You can contact him at (817) 390-7397. E-mail:
sportszone(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the Star-Telegram's online
services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
