<HEADER>
A2395 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FILM-PROFILE-O'KEEFE-     01-28 0767
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-PROFILE-O'KEEFE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ACTRESS JODI O'KEEFE, CLOSET KLUTZ, IS ON A ROLL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JANE GANAHL  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Good news for teen-age girls throughout the
land! Actress Jodi Lyn O'Keefe, she of the perfect hair, teeth and
bod _ not to mention a face like Venus _ is a klutz.
</P>
<P>
   ``In every sense of the word, completely and totally,'' she says
solemnly, sitting in a hotel conference room in San Francisco as
she promotes her new film, ``She's All That.''
</P>
<P>
   ``And I don't care who knows it!''
</P>
<P>
   While filming a recent episode of ``Nash Bridges'' here (she
plays Don Johnson's daughter), the 20-year-old was wearing only a
moleskin in the shower, when she slipped and hit her head _ hard.
``Everyone came running over to me _ `Are you OK?' _ and I was
screaming at them, `I'm fine, I'm fine, and I'm NAKED!' It was bad,
though. I had this big old bruise on my forehead that made me look
like something out of `Star Trek.'''
</P>
<P>
   And while filming ``She's All That'' _ in which she plays an
evil high school senior named Taylor _ O'Keefe had a few other
mishaps. Like during a love scene with Matthew Lillard
(``Scream''), when he flipped her over and she cracked her head on
the headboard; another scene called for her to leap into Lillard's
arms, and every time she did, her tube top fell down.
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course I can blame that one on my lack of ... you know...''
and she bursts out laughing. Say what? Taylor is presented as one
buxom babe.
</P>
<P>
   ``Let's talk about Wonderbras every day!'' says O'Keefe, who
talks 90 miles an hour, while poking at a chocolate on her plate.
``For this movie we're talking pushed-up, padded, silicone. You
know, the kind that comes out of a box. I would take them out and
throw them at people like bean bags!''
</P>
<P>
   O'Keefe is such a seasoned professional, having started acting
at 8, that there are only occasional glimpses _ like this one _
into her youthfulness. She grows serious again.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I'm trying to not be insecure about it. I'm planning to
have a career based on my acting skills rather than the size of my
chest.''
</P>
<P>
   Here's another reason for looks-obsessed girls to hope: O'Keefe
was once a geek.
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh, fully!'' she laughs. ``When I was a freshman, I was 5 feet
9 and totally skinny as a pole. Knock-knees and bad hair. Then over
that summer I grew up a little bit. Not that I was some super
beauty, but at least I didn't look like I was 10 anymore and had a
little self-confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   Having ``been there'' herself, O'Keefe has complete sympathy for
the shy, geeky young woman character in the movie that she, as the
reigning high school diva, is supposed to torture.
</P>
<P>
   ``Doing this scene where I was supposed to pour wine down Rachel
Cook's dress was really hard,'' she admits. ``I felt like this
horrible monster. I apologized to her 100 times until she had to
tell me it's OK, just pour the damn wine.''
</P>
<P>
   O'Keefe joined the cast of ``Nash Bridges'' at age 16, when she
moved to California from New Jersey to take the job. Her mother
moved with her and stayed until she turned 18. Now in its fourth
season, O'Keefe's character has supposedly enrolled at the
University of California at Berkeley, although she's still seen
frequently.
</P>
<P>
   What about published rumors that she and Johnson were an item at
one time? O'Keefe politely declares that Johnson is a rumor magnet
because ``women love him. And I do, too _ but not that way. I mean,
I love his whole family.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
</P>
<ANNOTATION>
   (STORY CAN END HERE. OPTIONAL MATERIAL FOLLOWS.) &QL; 
</ANNOTATION>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   O'Keefe says she has minded rumor items about her only ``because
of how they impact my family back home. But I always tell them, if
you want to know the truth, call me. I'm getting sort of used to it
myself.''
</P>
<P>
   O'Keefe has an apartment in San Francisco and Los Angeles, where
she goes in her spare time.
</P>
<P>
   As for her college plans, O'Keefe says she plans to attend at
some point, ``but not for a while. I figure I should strike while
the iron is hot. While the opportunity is there, and the work.
School will always be there. I was thinking Mills College, because
I really love it here.''
</P>
<P>
   She is waiting for the ink to dry on a couple of new movie deals
before she can talk about them. But she has high hopes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really admire actresses like Meryl Streep; I would love to
have a career like hers. And Natalie Wood _ I thought she was so
beautiful. And I want to make a movie with Al Pacino someday. Maybe
that sounds ridiculous now, but if I keep saying it, maybe it will
come true!''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
