   &UR; SUPER BOWL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-CHANDLER (Miami) _ Feature on Chris Chandler, the
journeyman N.F.L. quarterback who has come into his own on the
Falcons. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SUPER-TURNOVERS (Miami) _ Getting inside Sunday's game, by
looking at the turnover issue. Eight of the last 10 winners of the
Super Bowl went into the game with a better turnover ratio than
their opponent. In this game, it's Atlanta that has the better
numbers; in fact, their turnover ratio is the best in the NFL. By
Thomas George.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BRONCOS-ROBINSON (Miami) _ Small feature on Greg Robinson,
the former Jets' defensive coordinator who now runs the Broncos
defense. By Gerald Eskenazi.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SUPER-NOTEBOOK (Miami) _ A Super Bowl notebook.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BLACK-COACHES (Miami) _ The fact that the NFL seems unable
to increase its small of black head coaches has now been
well-documented. But a missing element in all this has been the
lack of comments from the players in a league in which over half
the players are black. By William C. Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER SPORTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-BERKOW-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column on
Latrell Sprewell, who made a strong debut in the Knicks' exhibition
game at Madison Square Garden Wednesday night. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-RANGERS-HURRICANES (Charlotte, N.C.) _ N.Y. Rangers at
Carolina, 7 p.m. ET start. By Joe Lapointe.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-BRUINS (Boston) _ N.J. Devils at Boston, 7 p.m. ET
start. By Alex Yannis.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-AUSTRALIA (Melbourne) _ Action at the Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PHOENIX (Phoenix) _ First round of the Phoenix Open, with
all eyes on Mr. 59, otherwise known as David Duval. By Clifton
Brown.
