<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sweep your valentine away: Super ideas for quick getaways
 &HT;    EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, Jan. 31.
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   OK, all you folks focused like lasers on today's Super Bowl.
Here's a reminder of something important that may be sneaking up on
you while you're doing the Dirty Bird: Valentine's Day is but two
weeks away. With all that money you saved by not buying
ridiculously expensive game tickets, you can splurge for a V-Day
weekend getaway.
</P>
<P>
   Here are a few options:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Unicoi Lodge at Unicoi State Park near Helen has a weekend
package that won't put a big dent in your budget. A one-night
package for two, including lodging, dinner, evening entertainment
and breakfast, is $169; stay two nights for $199 (another dinner
and breakfast included). On Feb. 13, there will be a special
Valentine's dinner as well as a concert by Bob and Melody Thomason,
who perform a blend of traditional songs from the Appalachians and
the British Isles using guitar, banjo and mountain dulcimer.
Packages available the evenings of Feb. 12 and 13. 706-878-2201,
Ext. 268.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Chateau Elan Winery &AMP; Resort in Braselton has created three
romantic packages available the evening of Feb. 13. The Inn
Package, $399, includes a deluxe room, a four-course dinner for two
with wine in the Versailles Room or Cafe Versailles, a souvenir
Valentine's-label bottle of Chateau Elan wine and breakfast buffet
for two in the Versailles Room. The Le Clos Package, $569, includes
a suite at the Inn, a seven-course dinner for two with wine at Le
Clos, souvenir wine and breakfast buffet. The Spa Package, $709,
includes a room at the European-style Spa, a five-course dinner for
two with wine and breakfast at Fleur-de-Lis, a dozen long-stemmed
roses, a bottle of champagne, use of the Spa whirlpool, steam,
sauna and fitness facilities, plus the choice of a Swedish massage,
deep-cleaning facial or manicure and pedicure. A jazz band will
play in the Atrium of the Inn at Chateau Elan 7 p.m.-midnight (cash
bar). 770-932-0900, Ext. 41.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The Cypress Inn _ which overlooks the Waccamaw River in
Conway, S.C. _ offers couples the opportunity to renew their
wedding vows during the Second Annual Valentine Weekend. The
romantic candlelight ceremony begins at noon Feb. 13. The packages,
$280-$330, include hors d'oeuvres and wine at check-in Feb. 12, a
ceremony on Feb. 13 with brunch following, accommodations for two
nights and breakfast. The AAA four-diamond bed-and-breakfast has 12
individually decorated rooms with Jacuzzi tubs. 1-800-575-5307.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The Inn on Main Street, a Victorian bed-and-breakfast in
Weaverville, N.C., invites couples to spend a night in romantically
decorated rooms in a 100-year-old house. Awaiting them will be a
dozen red roses, chilled French champagne and two tickets to the
Biltmore Estate in nearby Asheville. The package, available Feb.
12-13 or Feb. 13-14, is $350 (slightly higher for a king bed, lower
without the champagne). 1-877-873-6074, or visit the Web site,
http://www
</P>
<P>
   .innonmain.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The historic General Morgan Inn in Greeneville, Tenn., hosts a
big band dance featuring the Charles Goodwin Orchestra for its
Valentine's Day weekend bash. After a 7:30 p.m. dinner in the grand
ballroom Feb. 13, guests can dance to swing tunes from 9 p.m. until
midnight. Then, couples retire to deluxe rooms at the historic
hotel, which is decorated with period furnishings dating to the
late 1700s. The next morning, the General's Grand Continental
Breakfast Buffet will be served. Cost is $189 per couple.
1-800-223-2679, Ext. 114.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The Tutwiler in Birmingham, the 84-year-old hotel where
Tallulah Bankhead honeymooned, will celebrate Valentine's weekend
by offering an overnight package and dinner. Available Feb. 12 or
13, the package includes deluxe accommodations, chilled champagne
in the room, a rose-on-pillow turn-down, breakfast and valet
parking for $165 per couple. Add dinner, and the price comes to
$275. The Tutwiler, a Wyndham Grand Heritage Hotel, features marble
floors, crystal chandeliers, fine art and turn-of-the-century
antiques. 1-800-845-1787.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Nashville's turn-of-the-century Union Station, another Wyndham
Grand Heritage Hotel, will offer its Valentine's Package through
February. The price is $405 for a deluxe room and $305 for a suite
(per room per night, based on double occupancy) and includes
accommodations, a bottle of champagne with two souvenir flutes,
chocolate truffles, a dozen long-stemmed roses, a breakfast buffet
and, for those spending the night Feb. 13, free admission to the
second annual Cupid's Ball. The ball will be held in the train
station-turned-hotel's atrium lobby, which features a 65-foot-long
barrel-vaulted ceiling with original stained glass panels. The
lobby also has oak-accented doors and walls, a black marble
fountain, a marble-enhanced fireplace and bas-relief figures
trimmed with gold. 1-800-331-2123.
</P>
<P>
   _ Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
