<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   STEEL _ Looking into a report that AK Steel has filed a federal
lawsuit against its own union. Could be the first salvo in long
battle over the new union's stated intent to affiliate the union
with the United Steelworkers of America, which AK Steel management
despises. Staff, Dayton Daily News). 12.
</P>
<P>
   PBP-NASA _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The Treasure Coast has moved
a step closer to getting a long awaited NASA business incubator,
officials said Thursday. Indian River Community College and five
other community colleges around the state, will each get $300,000
in NASA money for the programs. The Fort Pierce college is
expecting the state legislature to set aside another $600,000 so it
can construct a building for the incubator. The incubators provide
support to entrepreneurs who are commercializing NASA-developed
patents. (Bhatt, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   BANKAM-EARNINGS _ BankAmerica provides reassurance to analysts
about its earnings outlook and announces deal to buy a unit of
Associates First Capital. (C hambers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   IRS-VISIT _ If you live more than 40 miles from the nearest
Internal Revenue Service, the IRS may be coming for a neighborly
visit to help you file your 1998 income taxes. Don't panic. They're
not coming to your house but, beginning Monday, it will send vans
with to 24 cities in Georgia that are more than 40 miles from the
nearest IRS office. Monday, the vans will visit the first three
cities: Elberton, LaGrange and Tifton. (Tharpe, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   LOCKHEED-LAYOFFS _ About 280 workers at Lockheed Martin's
Marietta plant face layoffs as the company copes with stalled
C-130J sales and other cost pressures. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SOCOMPANY-CHINA _ Southern Co. is expected to buy into a
provincial Chinese power plant operator and builder that is selling
$285 million in shares to private investors. Southern is expected
to be the main participant in an initial public offering thet is
being closely watched as a barometer of the Chbinbese investment
picture in 1999. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
