<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-28 18:29 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2862 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      01-28 0608
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release FRIDAY AMs, January 29, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-HUSSEIN (Amman, Jordan) _ The stunning turn of events
inside the palace of King Hussein sends shockwaves through the
nation and the region, where Jordan is caught between Iraq and
Israel. By Charles M. Sennott. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA-DAMAGE (Armenia, Colombia) _ President Andres Pastrana
decides to personally direct the relief effort in Colombia. He
sends thousands of troops to curtail looting by both survivors and
opportunists. By Richard Chacon. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMPEACHMENT (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) -- Senate stumbles over terms for
deposing three witnesses. Democrats object to public showing of
videotaped testimony from Monica Lewinsky. By Bob Hohler. 1500
words.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-AGREE (Washington) -- A vote in favor of a motion to
proceed with the impeachment trial signals the end of
bipartisanship. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON-MAYOR (Washington) _ The rap from some quarters on
Anthony A. Williams, Washington's new mayor, is that he isn't black
enough. Others say he isn't political enough. This week, Williams,
a bow-tied bureaucrat, tried to prove he is both, and now he's in
trouble. by Mary Leonard. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CANCER-ADVANCES (Undated) _ Researchers say chemotherapy before
surgery produces better results with breast cancer. And colon
cancer treated with vaccines developed from a patient's own cells
shows hope. By Richard A. Knox. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   HARVARD-TEACHING (Undated) _ Harvard University, as part of a
long-term plan to change the way it educates students and conducts
research, will spend millions of dollars during the next five years
for new science programs. By Adam Pertman. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-AUTO-INSURE (Boston) _ Biggest auto insurers doing business
in Bay State file nearly identical plans to sharply scale back
their discounts for good drivers to 5 percent. By Bruce Mohl. 750
words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-RAPE-SETTLEMENT (Boston) _ State agency to pay an undisclosed
