slips fell Thursday on Universal Music Group's sales staff with
about 200 layoffs, eliminating a third of that division's 600 jobs.
The move by the world's largest music company represents the second
phase in the massive restructuring at UMG, which cut 500 jobs last
week at its A&AMP;M, Geffen, Mercury and Motown labels. By Dave McNary.
(Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
