<P>
   FAN-PSYCHOLOGY _ ATLANTA _ Mix in a little tribalism, a little
sexuality, a little patriotism and a little ancient religion and
you have the makings of a sports fan. Sports, unlike any other
modern institution, evokes the deepest human emotions and genetic
social maps, creating a bonding in a community and in a family
seldom paralleled in today's world _ short of war. Psychologists
and fans talk about why fans act the way they do. (Lore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   DIRTYBIRD _ The dirty bird goes national. A look at how the
dirty bird phenomenon started and grew. Planning to talk to Billy
White Shoes Johnson; Jamal Anderson and his sister; a dance
instructor; the rapper who sings the song etc. The story will also
compare and contrast the Dirty Bird with the Funky Chicken and the
Bird and look at other celebratory fads like the Super Bowl
Shuffle, the Ickey shuffle and Denver's salute. (Suggs, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTO ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHBEACH _ The Super Bowl party is for the elite only, and so,
in increasing measure, is South Miami Beach. Ten years ago it was a
rundown stretch of seedy hotels populated by Mariel boatlift
refugees and aging New York retirees. Today it's an international
hot-spot, home of jet-setters, fashion models, movie stars and
various beautiful people. What happened to the folks who used to
live there? (MWilliams, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
