<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SUPER-COLLINS (Miami) _ The Atlanta Falcons' largely
unheralded offensive line has been a big part of the team's
success, opening holes for Jamal Anderson and protecting the
always-vulnerable Chris Chandler. One of the keys to the
improvement of that line has been the emergence of Calvin Collins,
a second-year player from Texas A&AMP;M and Beaumont, Texas. By JODY
GOLDSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-TEXANS (Miami) _ The Atlanta Falcons are loaded with Texas
connections, from Dan Reeves with the Dallas Cowboys to Billy White
Shoes Johnson, Tommy Nobis, Harold Richardson. A look at the Texas
connection for both teams. By JODY GOLDSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SUPER-NEIL (Miami) _ The Denver Broncos' offensive line has
quietly emerged as one of the best in pro football, thanks in part
to former University of Texas standout Dan Neil, a second-year
player. By JOHN McCLAIN.
</P>
