<HEADLINE>
IOC BOARD THREATENS TO RESIGN 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (i, a and s coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JOHN POWERS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The International Olympic Committee's executive board will quit
if its colleagues do not expel five members implicated in the Salt
Lake City payoff scandal, vice president Richard Pound of Canada
warned Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Though four members have already stepped down amid the worst
scandal in modern Olympic history, three others _ Jean-Claude Ganga
of the Republic of Congo, Lamine Keita of Mali and Agustin Arroyo
of Ecuador _ have vowed to contest their expulsion before the full
115-member body in Lausanne, Switzerland in March.
</P>
<P>
   ``If these people show up and fight and can persuade two-thirds
of the membership not to expel them, you'll have the entire
