<HEADLINE>
A PATRIOT DOES HER PART
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   When  &UR; Cher &LR;  sings the national anthem at the Super Bowl on
Sunday _ prerecorded and backed by an 80-piece orchestra _ she's
not going to wear one of her everyday navel-flashing side-slit
ensembles.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to be really respectful of the song,'' she said at a
news conference. ``I will be completely covered. This is the
biggest single honor I've ever had.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LISTENING TO NATIONAL HISTORY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   National Public Radio's ``All Things Considered'' begins
broadcasting ``Lost &AMP; Found Sound,'' a yearlong anthology of the
sounds of the 20th century on January 29. The producers of the
series,  &UR; Davia Nelson &LR; ,  &UR; Nikki Silva &LR;  and  &UR; Jay Allison, &LR;  hope to
combine historic recordings of momentous events, documentaries
about developments in sound (the laugh track, for example), &LR;  and
the everyday sounds of the nation at work or at home, as captured
in amateur recordings. The sound designer is  &UR; Randy Thom &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   The project's ``Quest for Sound'' feature, which begins today,
will include home recordings submitted by listeners around the
country. The recordings might include such treasures as unusual
answering-machine messages, recorded letters from wartime, cylinder
recordings, audio pen-pal postcards, do-it-yourself discs made in
amusement parks. Suitable contributions will be included in future
``Quest for Sound'' installments.
</P>
<P>
   Prospective donors of sound snippets should call (202) 408-0300.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASHES OF LIGHT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   If San Francisco Mayor  &UR; Willie Brown  &LR; is such a perfectionist,
gripes  &UR; Michael Easton &LR; , why are his lights out of synch? Easton,
who lives at McAllister and Grove streets, watches the nightly
spectacle as the Civic Center building lights go on with no
apparent rhythm.
</P>
<P>
   City Hall lights are first, followed by lower lights on the War
Memorial Building, then upper lights on the Opera House, then upper
lights on the War Memorial then, last, lower lights on the Opera
House. At Davies Hall, the lights go off when the curtain comes
down; if there's no performance, there are no lights.
</P>
<P>
   If a simple ``Let there be light'' did it in the Bible, unison
ought to be easy for Brown.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ More on the French medal front: Wine importer, winery owner
and all-round wine maven  &UR; Kermit Lynch &LR;  of Berkeley was awarded the
Chevalier de l'Ordre de Merite Agricole by the French government
earlier this month. Cited for his contributions to French
viticulture and his 1988 book ``Adventures on the Wine Route,''
Lynch was decorated by the French consul general, who bestowed upon
him a round medal with star and bright-colored ribbon.
</P>
<P>
   He doubts he will wear it in the United States, but in France,
where Lynch spends six months a year, official functions of wine
syndicates and various bureaucracies will provide suitable
occasions. ``When I take part in something like that,'' he said,
the medal ``will give me a little more punch.''
</P>
<P>
   _ General  &UR; Norman Schwarzkopf &LR;  told People magazine that if
there were ever a movie about his life, the guy to play him would
be  &UR; Danny DeVito &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _ One more cup reference, further beclouding  &UR; Tom Wolfe &LR; 's
mention of ``that thing with the cup'':  &UR; Delia Garigan &LR;  submits
``Don't buy sugar? You've just got to touch my cup,'' from  &UR; Fats &LR; 
 &UR; Waller &LR; 's ``Honeysuckle Rose.'' More groceries:  &UR; Hobie McQuarrie &LR; 
bought a package of Allegra pasta, the package emblazoned with
``Imported'' in English, &LR;  and, in Italian, ``Qualita Superiore.'' A
close inspection of the back of the package reveals that it's made
in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ After 17 years, wife No. 4, 50-year-old  &UR; Heather &LR; , has filed
for divorce from  &UR; Woody Allen &LR; 's father-in-law, 69-year-old  &UR; Andre &LR; 
 &UR; Previn &LR; , says the Boston Herald.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Melanie Lawrence &LR;  suggests a 40th Barbie anniversary
commemorative Barbie of Willendorf, based on the Stone Age
sculpture of a mother goddess, ``topped by mud-sculpted hair,
covered with spirals painted in blue ... and best of all, dominated
by a genuine, glorious, round, fecund, basketball-sized stomach.
Truly a role model to inspire our daughters.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``She can hardly get through an open door without explicit
instructions.''
</P>
<P>
   _ William Lee Scott on the intellect of his fellow ``Black and
White'' cast member Claudia Schiffer, in the Calgary Sun.
</P>
</TEXT>
