with a protractor, string and a weight. Using mathematical
calculations, Gravenstine devised a way to use the device to
measure the height of buildings. Her work is part of a portfolio
she needs to present in order to graduate from her high school.
(Suzanne DeChillo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
