1-28 -- Looters carry goods stolen for damaged stores Wednesday
night. Angered by delays in the delivery of food and other
assistance after one of the worst earthquakes in more than a
century, residents in this town looted supermarkets and stores and
threw stones at soldiers and police officers. (Chang W. Lee/New
York Times Photo)
