century, residents in this town looted supermarkets and stores and
threw stones at soldiers and police officers. (Chang W. Lee/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) ARMENIA, Colombia -- Jan. 28, 1999 -- COLOMBIA-QUAKE,
1-28 -- Leticia Cevallos in a makeshift tent in front of her
damaged house on Wednesday. President Andres Pastrana formally
declared a state of disaster for the region Tuesday, describing
Monday's earthquake as ``a grave wound'' to the well-being of the
country. Over 1,000 people are believed to have died. (Chang W.
Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
