<P>
   (NYT10) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 28, 1999 -- MAYORS-GUNS, 1-28 --
Edward Randel, mayor of Philadelphia, speaks to reporters on
Thursday. In a sign that the assault on the gun industry is gaining
political momentum, Randel announced that mayors from around the
country are helping prepare Federal legislation designed to slow
the circulation of illegal guns and are urging more cities to sue
