<HEADLINE>
ANOTHER $1.5 MILLION IN DAMAGES AWARDED TO DUSTIN HOFFMAN  (DW)
</HEADLINE>
  c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ A judge awarded $1.5 million in punitive damages
Thursday to the actor Dustin Hoffman, doubling the amount Los
Angeles Magazine must pay him for using a digitally altered
photograph of him in a 1997 fashion article.
</P>
<P>
   Judge Dickran Tevrizian of U.S. District Court here, who found
in Hoffman's favor last week and awarded him $1.5 million in
compensatory damages, issued the ruling after hearing arguments.
</P>
<P>
   Hoffman sued the magazine over its use in its March 1997 issue
of his photograph from his role in the 1982 movie ``Tootsie.''
</P>
</TEXT>
